In England, in the seven days to 09 December, there were 293,521 new confirmed cases (519.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 02 December, there were 274,673 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 7% (18,848 extra cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 14 December is 9,275,513 (16,402.3 cases per 100,000 population).
